  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\nAs a user, I want to log  into Status using an account created on another device so that I can use my account on both devices.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: The iOS keyboard can't be hidden, and blocks the `Password` field.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3212454/41873228-5f44a828-7892-11e8-968a-a845b64c9268.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nI expect to be able to hide the keyboard so I can select the `Password` field so I can enter my password.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nI can't hide the keyboard so I can select the `Password` field so I can enter my password.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Tap \"I already have an account\"\r\n- Enter a seed phrase\r\n- Notice you cannot hide the `keyboard` to view/select the `Password` field\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: Provide an option to hide the keyboard so users can select the password field\r\n\r\n- Add a button to hide the keyboard.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.20 (6075)\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: iOS on iPad\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat)\r\n```\r\n...\r\n```",
